President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived in Lagos State on Thursday. Buhari touched down at the Presidential Lounge of the Murtala Muhammed Airport in Lagos in the early hours of the day. Also Read:Â SERAP Lists Six Court Judgments Disobeyed By Buhari Administration The President was received at the airport by Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu and other officials. During the visit, Buhari is expected to commission naval boats and helicopters and also attend the book launch of a former Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bisi Akande. On Wednesday, the Lagos State Traffic Management Authority (LASTMA) has announced the closure of some major roads ahead of the visit.